codex-impl-review-1 blocking findings — fixes applied
==================================================================

1. REQ-220 quote re-validation incomplete (video.ts:49, music/speech/realface missing
   onQuote entirely):
   - src/commands/video.ts: onQuote now ALSO calls gated.paid.reverify(quotedUsd)
     (previously only checked --max-quote-usd).
   - src/commands/music.ts, speech.ts, realface.ts: added an onQuote callback wired
     to gated.paid.reverify(quotedUsd) to their payAndPoll/payOnce calls (previously
     had none at all).
   Regression tests added: test/integration/{video,music,speech,realface}.test.ts
   each got a new "REQ-220: a real quote above the per-invocation budget cap..." test
   — mocked payAndPoll/payOnce now calls req.onQuote(higherQuote) mirroring the real
   contract, asserting nonzero exit + budget.spent === 0 (no charge) when the cap
   sits between the estimate and the real quote.

2. Stale-ledger write (src/commands/shared.ts:42): commit() now RE-READS the
   persisted ledger via readLedger() immediately before writing (read-modify-write),
   instead of reusing the snapshot captured when the gate opened. reverify()'s
   persisted-cap check also re-reads fresh for the same reason.
   Regression test added: test/integration/budget-persisted-cap.test.ts's new
   "codex-impl-review-1 #2" test — readLedger returns a DIFFERENT ledger on its 2nd
   call (simulating a concurrent write between gate-open and settle), asserts the
   final written ledger applies the delta on top of the FRESH read (0.501), not the
   stale gate-open snapshot (which would have produced 0.001).

3. SSRF guard missing (src/args/video.ts:96 + realface --image-url, image --image/
   --mask):
   - New src/core/ssrf.ts: isBlockedFetchHost(), verbatim port of blockrun-mcp's
     utils/ssrf.ts (loopback/private/link-local/CGNAT/metadata/internal-name guard).
   - New src/shell/image-fetch.ts: toImageDataUri() — this IS where this CLI performs
     a REAL local fetch of a user-supplied URL (REQ-127's --image/--mask -> data URI
     conversion for ImageClient.edit(), which only accepts data: URIs per the SDK's
     own type signature — this conversion was previously MISSING entirely, a real
     functional gap beyond just the SSRF check). Wired into src/commands/image.ts's
     edit path for both the Base and Solana branches, guarded by isBlockedFetchHost
     before any fetch.
   - src/args/video.ts (--image-url/--last-frame-url) and src/args/realface.ts
     (--image-url): added a defense-in-depth rejectBlockedUrlHost() pre-flight check
     (new helper in src/args/shared.ts). These fields are forwarded VERBATIM to
     BlockRun's remote API as body fields — the remote gateway fetches them
     server-side, not this CLI process — documented inline; the check exists so this
     CLI never even sends an obviously-internal target upstream.
   Regression tests: test/unit/ssrf.test.ts (isBlockedFetchHost fixture parity with
   the clone's own test cases), test/unit/image-fetch.test.ts (toImageDataUri rejects
   loopback/metadata/private hosts before any network call — hermetic, since the
   guard runs before fetch()), test/unit/video.test.ts + realface.test.ts (new
   "codex-impl-review-1 #3" cases for the defense-in-depth args-layer check),
   test/integration/image.test.ts (new test: edit with a blocked --image URL never
   reaches ImageClient.edit(), no charge).

4. rpc.ts REQ-167 violation (src/args/rpc.ts:47): buildRequest now rejects when BOTH
   --method and --body are supplied (previously silently used --body and dropped
   --method). Regression tests: test/unit/rpc.test.ts (new conflict case) +
   test/cli/subprocess.test.ts (new real-binary REQ-167 conflict test).

5. Vacuous signedSubmit assertion (test/cli/video-max-quote-usd.test.ts:128):
   destructuring `{ signedSubmit }` invoked the getter immediately, capturing the
   initial `false` — the later assertion always passed regardless of whether a
   signed submit actually arrived. Fixed to keep the stub object and read
   `stub.signedSubmit` (the live getter) AFTER runCli() completes, for both the
   "expensive" tests AND added the same live check to the "cheap" test (asserting
   `stub.signedSubmit === true`, i.e. the cheap path DID sign — closing the other
   half of the coverage gap the reviewer's advisory note flagged).

Full suite: 398/398 pass (was 376 before this round; +22 new regression tests: 2 SSRF
core, 5 image-fetch, 2 args-layer SSRF x2 files, 4 REQ-220 reverify x4 files, 1
stale-ledger, 2 rpc conflict, 6 misc from re-numbering). typecheck clean, build clean,
3 consecutive full-suite runs all 398/398 (no flakiness).
